Array:
Array is an indexed collection of fixed no of homogeneous data elements
main adv- we can represent a huge no of data using a single variable
main disadv- we cannot change the size of array

representation :
1d array -> int[] x; int x[]; int []x;
2d array -> int[][] x; int x[][]; int[] []x; int []x[]; int [] x[]; int [][]x;

array creation :
every array in java is an object hence we can create array using new operator : int[] x = new int[3];
the size of array must be specified by an integer value instead of other data types
we can also specify the size by '0' value
if we try to specify the size with negative value then we will get runtime exception -> NegativeArraySizeException